      "Maintain BMNR cash-secured put ladder as Bitcoin holds above $62,300 structural level with Tom Lee bullish on crypto outlook",
      "Monitor oil closely as unexpected inventory draws could pressure the $100 stagflation threshold despite current stability",
      "Consider reducing Maturity sector overweight if housing weakness spreads to broader consumer discretionary given NAHB concerns about material costs and buyer traffic"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Unexpected crude oil inventory draw of -0.9M barrels vs +2.1M expected suggests tighter supply despite geopolitical headline risks.",
      "NAHB Housing Index dropped to 34 vs 38 prior and 37 expected, with builders citing Iran war and energy costs as key headwinds.",
      "Dollar at 6-week lows on Iran peace talk speculation, providing tailwind for risk assets and commodities.",
      "Bitcoin holding key support levels despite geopolitical stress, with institutional flows (Bhutan moving 250 BTC) suggesting continued adoption."
